---
// src/pages/privacy.astro
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import NavBlock from "../components/NavBlock.astro";

const effectiveDate = "June 2, 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Quirgs"
  description="Privacy policy for the Quirgs AI governance skills registry."
  terminalPath="~/privacy"
>
  <NavBlock currentPath="/privacy/" />

  <div class="line">
    <span class="prompt">admin@quirgs</span><span class="path">~/privacy</span
    ><span class="text-bright">$</span>&nbsp;cat privacy.md
  </div>
  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>

  <div class="detail-header">
    <h1 class="text-bright">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="tagline">How we handle information on quirgs.com.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="terminal-body" style="padding: 0;">
    <p><strong class="text-bright">Effective date:</strong> {effectiveDate}</p>

    <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
    <p>
      Quirgs (<strong class="text-bright">quirgs.com</strong>) is a registry of
      AI governance skills and reference guides. The site is operated as a sole
      proprietorship. Contact: <a href="/support/">/support/</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>2. What we collect</h2>
    <p>
      We do not collect personal data through forms, accounts, or sign-ups.
      quirgs.com has no authentication layer and no user-submitted content.
    </p>
    <p>
      We do collect anonymous, aggregated usage data through the analytics tools
      described in Section 4. This data cannot be used to identify you
      personally.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Cookies</h2>
    <p>
      The following cookies may be set when you visit quirgs.com. All are
      functional or analytics in nature. No advertising or cross-site tracking
      cookies are set.
    </p>

    <table class="cookie-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Cookie</th>
          <th>Provider</th>
          <th>Purpose</th>
          <th>Duration</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>_ga</code></td>
          <td>Google Analytics 4</td>
          <td>Registers a unique ID to generate statistical data on how you use the site.</td>
          <td>2 years</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>_ga_&lt;ID&gt;</code></td>
          <td>Google Analytics 4</td>
          <td>Used by Google Analytics to persist session state.</td>
          <td>2 years</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>__cf_bm</code></td>
          <td>Cloudflare</td>
          <td>Bot management. Distinguishes legitimate visitors from automated traffic.</td>
          <td>30 minutes</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>_cfuvid</code></td>
          <td>Cloudflare</td>
          <td>Rate limiting and abuse prevention at the network edge.</td>
          <td>Session</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p>
      Google Analytics data is processed by Google LLC under Google's privacy
      policy (<a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">policies.google.com/privacy</a>).
      Cloudflare cookies are set by Cloudflare, Inc. and governed by Cloudflare's
      privacy policy (<a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/</a>).
    </p>
    <p>
      Cloudflare Web Analytics is also active on this site. Unlike traditional
      analytics, it does not set cookies or collect personal data — it uses
      edge-side aggregation only.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Analytics</h2>
    <p>
      We use two analytics tools to understand site usage:
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong class="text-bright">Google Analytics 4</strong> — Collects
      anonymized page view, session, and interaction data. IP addresses are
      anonymized. Data is retained for 14 months. You can opt out via the
      <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong class="text-bright">Cloudflare Web Analytics</strong> — A
      privacy-first, cookieless analytics tool. Collects aggregate page view
      data at the network edge. No personal data or cookies are used.
    </p>
    <p>
      This site is also registered with <strong class="text-bright">Google Search Console</strong>,
      which provides search performance data (e.g., which queries surface
      quirgs.com in Google Search). Search Console does not set cookies on your
      browser — it only processes data on Google's servers.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Third-party services</h2>
    <p>
      Skills distributed through quirgs.com link to external sources (GitHub
      Gists). Clicking those links takes you off quirgs.com and into GitHub's
      privacy policy. We have no control over data collected by third-party
      sites.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Data retention</h2>
    <p>
      We do not store personal data on our own servers. Google Analytics data
      is retained for 14 months per Google's default setting. Cloudflare Web
      Analytics data is retained per Cloudflare's standard policy.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      If you are located in the European Economic Area, UK, or California, you
      may have rights to access, correct, or delete data held about you under
      GDPR, UK GDPR, or CCPA. Because we do not directly store personal data,
      requests relating to Google Analytics data should be directed to Google.
      Contact us at <a href="/support/">/support/</a> with any questions.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy as our analytics tooling or data practices
      change. The effective date at the top will reflect the most recent
      revision. Continued use of quirgs.com after an update constitutes
      acceptance of the revised policy.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="line">&nbsp;</div>
  <div>
    Questions? See <a href="/support/">/support/</a>.
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .cookie-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 16px 0 24px 0;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }

  .cookie-table th,
  .cookie-table td {
    border: 1px solid var(--term-border);
    padding: 8px 12px;
    text-align: left;
    vertical-align: top;
  }

  .cookie-table th {
    color: var(--text-bright);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
    font-weight: bold;
  }

  .cookie-table td code {
    color: var(--accent-green);
    background: #09090b;
    padding: 1px 5px;
    border-radius: 3px;
    border: 1px solid var(--term-border);
    font-family: inherit;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .cookie-table {
      font-size: 0.78rem;
    }

    .cookie-table th,
    .cookie-table td {
      padding: 6px 8px;
    }
  }
</style>
